<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-02-07T10:15:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-02-07T10:15:00-05:00" n="733" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d733">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">800.24/1512: Airgram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi>
                                    (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Winant</hi></persName>)
                                    <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-02-07T16:15:00+01:00">February 7, 1944—4:15 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received February 15—1 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>A–153. In reply to statements on military supplies for Saudi Arabia,
                                quoted in Department’s A–5 of January 1, Foreign Office has now
                                answered as follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                    <p>“Thank you for your letter of the 13th January about military
                                        supplies for Saudi Arabia.</p>
                                    <p>“We are glad to note that agreement has been reached that
                                        such supplies are to be provided in substantially equal
                                        measure by the Government of the United States and by His
                                        Majesty’s Government.”</p>
                                </quote>
                            </p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Winant</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>